  "scraped_at": "2026-01-10T08:02:41.228837",
  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "~5% of patients on ≥40 mg daily of\nprednisone\nhave psychiatric symptoms\n[1]\nIncidence rises to just under 20% for patients receiving more ≥80 mg per day\nMechanism unproven but thought to be increased dopamine due to induction of tyrosin hydroxylase by corticosteroids\n[2]",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "prednisone",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Prednisone"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Time of onset variable\nMedian onset after 11.5-12.5 days\n[3]\n[4]\nCase reports of psychosis within one day after exposure\nWide range of possible psychiatric symptoms\nDelusions\nor\nhallucinations\nEuphoria\nMania\n,\ndepression\n,\nanxiety\nSevere cases may present with\nsuicidal ideation\n, violence, aggression",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "hallucinations",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Hallucinations"
        },
        {
          "text": "depression",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Depression"
        },
        {
          "text": "anxiety",
